<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Image, Hyperlink and Nested Table</title>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>My Web Page</h1>

    <img src="photo.jpg" alt="My Image" width="150">

    <p>
        Visit 
        <a href="https://www.google.com">Google</a>
    </p>

    <table border="1">
        <tr>
            <th>Name</th>
            <th>Details</th>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <td>Arafat</td>
            <td>
                <table border="1">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Age</th>
                        <th>City</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>18</td>
                        <td>Sangli</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table>

</body>
</html>
 
Simple code explanation
•	<!DOCTYPE html> — tells the browser this is an HTML5 page. 
•	<head> — contains page information. 
•	<title> — shows the title on the browser tab. 
•	<body> — visible content of the page. 
Image
<img src="..." alt="Sample Image">
•	img displays an image. 
•	src gives the image location. 
•	alt shows alternate text if image does not load. 
Hyperlink
<a href="https://www.google.com">Google</a>
•	a creates a link. 
•	href contains the destination URL. 
Table
<table border="1">
•	creates a table. 
•	tr = table row 
•	th = table heading 
•	td = table data 
Nested table
A table inside another table is called a nested table.
Here, the second table is placed inside the Details column.
